Package com.intellij.codeInspection.dataFlow.value

Interface VariableDescriptor

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DfaExpressionFactory.ArrayElementDescriptor, DfaExpressionFactory.AssertionDisabledDescriptor, DfaExpressionFactory.ThisDescriptor, SpecialField

    public interface VariableDescriptor
    Represents a descriptor of DfaVariableValue. Two variables are the same if they have the same descriptor and qualifier. A descriptor could be a PsiVariable, getter method, array element with given index, this expression, etc.

    Subclasses must have proper Object.equals(Object) and Object.hashCode() implementation or instantiation must be controlled to prevent creating equal objects. Also #toString() must return sane representation of the descriptor.
